document.title: 2020 New Jersey Student Learning Standards - Comprehensive Health and Physical Education Introduction

AA308E68B7EA48A891B4BEF7973918F6.description:
Evaluate the effectiveness of various strategies and skills that support an
individual’s ability to stop misusing and abusing drugs and remain drug free (counseling, peer
coaching, professional peer support group, and family counseling and support).

5351F156CCA1461E81C9F90A54454E32.description:
Utilize peer support and societal norms to formulate a health-enhancing
message to remain drug free.

3182CAA4F0F6412B8D336076A519ADC8.description:
Examine the drug laws, and regulations of the State of New Jersey, other
states and the affects; healthy and unhealthy on individuals, families, schools, and
communities (e.g., vaping products, e-cigarettes, cannabis and CBD products, opioids).

1A3693D07F3D44B8AF13C63E0DBA045E.description:
Analyze personal choices and behaviors related to substance use and misuse
to determine if they align with personal values and beliefs.

C3CAC124F5F14083A2807DA9F34D2A67.description:
Correlate duration of drug use and abuse to the incidence of drug-related
deaths, injuries, illness, and academic performance.

5511021EC3BF4FC0BB9F0BC17E2044E5.description:
Explore the relationship between individuals who abuse alcohol, tobacco, and
other drugs with an increase in intentional and unintentional health-risk behaviors.

887D9A805AF042A58C4CA394768A425E.description:
Compare and contrast the incidence and impact of commonly abused
substances on individuals and communities in the United States and other countries (e.g.,
tobacco, e-cigarettes, vaping products, alcohol, marijuana products, inhalants, anabolic
steroids, other drugs).

8F839AC325A34BE3857B8EDD7BDED365.description:
Examine the influences of drug use and misuse on an individual’s social,
emotional and mental wellness.

53B2578211674753A35865232B198958.description:
Analyze and discuss the evidence of the emotional and social impact of
mental health illness on families, communities, and states (e.g., depression, anxiety,
Alzheimer’s, panic disorders, eating disorders, impulse disorders).

B4AC8FF5372B4B63ACACAA37B594984F.description:
Analyze local, state, and international public health efforts to prevent and
control diseases and health conditions (e.g., vaccinations, immunizations, medical exams,
gene editing, artificial organ systems, prosthesis).

A375B28F7A104DD3B4701B959788FE81.description:
Evaluate emerging methods to diagnose and treat diseases and health
conditions that are common in young adults in the United States and in other countries (e.g.,
hepatitis, stroke, heart attacks, cancer,).

D5783BACA10D4D4F95CF11E7525E7E64.description:
Evaluate the benefits of biomedical approaches to prevent STIs (e.g.,
hepatitis B vaccine, HPV vaccine) and HIV (e.g., PrEP, PEP).

895405B3B1D64CF0A7C300D6AE9E9E89.description:
Provide examples of how drugs and medication mimic or block the action of
certain cells in the body, and how abusing drugs can affect the human body.

586F7652835A4D559EC62F1140833E06.description:
Develop a health care plan to help prevent and treat diseases and health
conditions one may encounter (e.g., breast/testicular exams, Pap smear, regular STIs testing,
HPV vaccine).

C438B8F4EF8F44A4A7B91F4385071671.description:
Analyze the short- and long-term consequences of sharing sexually explicit
images (sexting) or messages with individuals or posting online.

34A201FA8099435A8F48DB1B70440682.description: Evaluate strategies to use social media safely, legally, and respectfully.

6375838DB61C4C57A4D63CD2A18DBD0F.description:
Develop strategies to communicate effectively, safely, and with empathy when
using digital devices in a variety of situations (e.g., cyberbullying, sexting).

E0E954A0B0B349AEA1B364EAA887EC03.description:
Analyze recruitment tactics that sex traffickers/exploiters use to exploit
vulnerabilities and recruit youth.

656EAFECF7274B8ABC464BE59DE8DA61.description:
Describe the types of abuse (e.g., physical, emotional, psychological, financial,
sexual) and the cycle of violence as it relates to sexual abuse, domestic violence, dating
violence, and gender-based violence.

3308D0B0AC6D43368FB6FC4E28CF4D5C.description:
Identify the state and federal laws related to intimate partner and sexual violence
(e.g., sexual harassment, sexual abuse, sexual assault, domestic violence).

ED01133773DD4E618E2D653E60CF126B.description:
Investigate the relationship between alcohol, drug use, and motor vehicle crashes
and analyze the short- and long-term consequences of these actions.

4E3314315FFE42AAB583F5296EE0BBAB.description:
Summarize New Jersey motor vehicle laws and regulations, Safe Stops, and
determine their impact on health and safety (e.g., organ/tissue donation, traffic safety, avoid
driving distractors, seatbelt use, the use of hand-held devices).

3935FE36867D464C9E4DB7675BA5B355.description:
Analyze the short- and long-term consequences of sharing sexually explicit
images (sexting) or messages with individuals or posting online.

B51180D543664C4494A03F8FC24CEBDE.description:
Apply a thoughtful decision-making process to evaluate situations and influences
that could lead to healthy or unhealthy consequences (e.g., peers, media).

10F449A44FB04D1CBCECBCBA992F4519.description:
Research present trends in plant based and organic food choices and industries that
have shown an impact on lowering heart, cancer, diabetes, and other diseases.

B9EE4304CC054551BCF504DEBB5A7E47.description:
Implement strategies and monitor progress in achieving a personal nutritional
health plan.

8CE3C4384D48496CB23AC499EE7CABD8.description:
Analyze the unique contributions of each nutrient class (e.g., fats, carbohydrates,
protein, water, vitamins, minerals) to one’s health and fitness.

0D4AC45F9E114D4D93598C533FDE8F17.description:
Determine the relationship of nutrition and physical activity to weight loss, gain,
and maintenance.

B0D8EE660AB8405CBAE8C31EE01E371F.description:
Compare and contrast the nutritional trends, eating habits, and the impact of
marketing foods on adolescents and young adults nationally and worldwide.

1F840267A6E0452C9C148953677AF2D9.description:
Identify personal and community resources to explore career options related to
physical activity and health.

DCC559B15B334D3FB6D8D747B8652FBE.description:
Analyze the current and future impact of globalization and technology on the
influences of participation in sports, games, physical fitness activities, dance, gaming, outdoor
adventure, viewing sports, and social and emotional connections.

EBC76067F5814F8CA8DB17C63AAB46A4.description:
Implement a financial plan for participation in physical activity in the community
for self and family members.

2A6ADD73A2EF4017AC2BADE2A967A3D6.description:
Describe the social benefits gained from participating in physical activity (e.g.,
meeting someone, making friends, team work, building trust, experiencing something new).

0AA6DB3F847C4440BB373883E74F8CE0.description:
Exhibit responsible social behavior by including and cooperating with classmates
of all skill levels, assisting when needed, and collaborating respectfully to solve problems in
groups, teams, and in pairs during physical activity.

A9261260A19D46BD98DB6728A306C79A.description:
Examine building to a level of fitness to successfully participate in a range of
different physical activities during a lifetime.

A75BC02A0FB645DEBAB0DE801DDC47D1.description:
Develop a sense of openness and willingness when participating in physical
fitness activity to share and learn experiences from your own and other cultures.

27BCB38A54B34FAF8879D5DCC4B4D53A.description:
Apply and share a movement and physical fitness vocabulary that is intrinsic to
motivate oneself, to impact family, and others in a community.

616BBE76BF0249E297C55EC5FFF2BD94.description:
Analyze fitness knowledge in strength, conditioning, agility, and the
physiological responses of the energy systems effects on the mind and body before, during,
and after physical fitness activities.

EF5ADEA882E44188A8D2DD5C9D3402C3.description:
Determine the role of genetics, age, nutrition, sleep, the environment, and
exercise type on body composition and personal health (e.g., anabolic steroids, human growth
hormones, stimulants).

12B053107F0A460C8F6AB2A08E4E1CB1.description:
Design and implement a personal fitness plan, using evidence and evaluate how
that reflects knowledge and application of fitness-training principals (FITT) and the
components of skill related fitness.

03D2BE9A28F44E89BE5337A09A94F17E.description:
Respect and appreciate all levels of ability and encourage with care during all
physical activities.

CFFCB5232BD4426191053C3C65BDFE94.description:
Compare the short- and long-term benefits of physical activity and the impact on
wellness associated with physical, mental, emotional fitness through one's lifetime.

A73F1BD0CBE54CECA7A55CC14FFB7D32.description:
Develop rule changes to existing games, sports, and activities that enhance
participation, safety, and enjoyment.

6855692A32014CAEBA5E0E5DD96054BA.description:
Analyze etiquette, responsibilities, and preparation of players, officials,
trainers, and other participants and recommend strategies to improve their performance,
participation, and behavior.

658327AFB3F444B496AFBECE12C6A053.description:
Design, lead and critique rhythmic and physical activity that includes
variations in time, space, force, flow, and relationships (e.g., creative, cultural, social,
aerobics dance, fitness).

29312FB126C845CCAEC2965504D698A1.description:
Analyze application of force and motion (e.g., weight transfer, power, speed,
agility, range of motion) and modify movement to impact performance.

0093A3D95C054163A5C3A037DCBD7694.description:
Explain and demonstrate ways to apply movement skills from one game,
sport, aerobics, or recreational activity to another including striking skills (e.g., tennis,
badminton, ping pong, racquetball, pickle ball).

E5D76BE58A7A4C63A8A685A7C3C3A280.description:
Develop an action plan to assist individuals who have feelings of sadness, anxiety,
stress, trauma, or depression and share this information with individuals who will benefit.

5550ED06CE1646F48D8EC0E79EE39DFE.description:
Investigate how local, state, and global agencies are addressing health issues
caused by climate change and share this information in an appropriate setting.

81E2CDA5960A42B285A798B69BFDE942.description:
Describe how individuals and local, state, and global advocacy organizations
can collaborate to address common local and global health and social issues (e.g., hunger, clean
water, organ/tissue donation).

172FF2533C9A4298A1FE98586F48A78B.description:
Evaluate the validity of health information, resources, services, in school, home
and in the community.

7FCCCFB3AD8B4814B6C5159FBDE75349.description:
Analyze a variety of health products and services based on cost, availability,
accessibility, benefits and accreditation in the home, school, and in the community (e.g., suicide
prevention, breast/testicular self-examination, CPR/AED, life skills training, menstrual
products).

C504CB34B4F1446EBC23E383297F137A.description:
Identify medically accurate sources of information and local services that
provide contraceptive methods (including emergency contraception and condoms) and
pregnancy options (including parenting, abortion, safe haven, adoption, and prenatal care).

0C80D545114842CAB54F5785D8371B3A.description:
Explain the purpose of the Safe Haven Law and identify locations in your
community.

3BB08DA69DC44E129A4CAA276E6DBEB9.description:
Develop an advocacy plan for a health issue and share this information with
others who can benefit.

0CB581383002424E8392091FE3B47A74.description:
Analyze the opportunities available at home, in school, and in the community to
support the mental health of oneself or an individual.

3D27F2EB13DE475A8F5C1E02D0EA9811.description:
Analyze the state and federal laws related to minors’ ability to give and receive
sexual consent and their association with sexually explicit media.

F5AA685A46954310AE505E5FD116EB98.description:
Analyze the personal and societal factors that could keep someone from leaving
an unhealthy relationship.

1F23260B3BE643B8B1D4F53E2E99F55D.description:
Describe the human sexual response cycle, including the role of hormones and
pleasure.

62AE3714CD764539BBD45FBC7AADDB84.description:
Analyze factors that influence the choices, and effectiveness of safer sex
methods and contraception, including risk-reduction and risk-elimination strategies.

304370C7C5DF4334868EAEA54304D9F0.description: Analyze the benefits of abstinence from sexual activity using reliable resources.

602DC76CD63644A1813A6D3A39DA21A9.description:
Demonstrate ways to show respect for the boundaries of others as they relate to
intimacy and sexual behavior.

026BB2ECFD964247A75DC0BAEA3824B2.description:
Demonstrate strategies to prevent, manage, or resolve interpersonal conflicts
without harming self or others (defining and understanding the laws of consent and dating
violence).

306B3A961ECD4EA89DBB4CE47B6864EC.description:
Analyze current social issues affecting perceptions of sexuality, culture,
ethnicity, disability status and make recommendations to address those issues.

BDE159B5135040C199E9A607F5ABAAF0.description:
Advocate for school and community policies and programs that promote dignity
and respect for people of all genders, gender expressions, gender identities, and sexual
orientations.

5648DE78602742E5BEEDAD60C1DC9619.description:
Analyze the influences of peers, family, media, social norms and culture on the
expression of gender, sexual orientation, and identity.

5C0A6C59B3D1425DBD79F0189BF1EAE0.description:
Analyze and adapt mental and emotional health messages and communication
techniques to peers and other specific target audience (e.g., dimensions of health).

4A1D0D1DCD324988982FB79D59372068.description:
Describe strategies to appropriately respond to stressors in a variety of situations
(e.g., academics, relationships, shootings, death, car accidents, illness).

9264F7A4451C479698CDBAA5D4CC264B.description:
Analyze factors that influence the emotional and social impact of mental health
illness on the family.

69A6AE6272854E6F8C8007C386C41141.description:
Recognize one’s personal traits, strengths, and limitations and identify how to
develop skills to support a healthy lifestyle.

96F05945D54F42B0B33DEFEA5B71543C.description:
Evaluate parenting strategies used at various stages of child development
based on reliable sources of information.

79ADB5914D974393B0C87F9CB8C380D5.description: Assess the skills needed to be an effective parent.

61E4DB9FB1004AE18D1DAE3EE86640FE.description:
Analyze the emotional, social, physical, and financial effects of being a teen or
young adult parent.

89834722CEA24479B825070BA8DF9B11.description:
Analyze personal and societal factors that can influence decisions about
pregnancy options, including parenting, abortion, safe haven, and adoption.

0AA332D80C774EC39DD41B547AFAB160.description:
Analyze factors that can impact the health of a baby (e.g., fetal alcohol
syndrome, sudden infant death syndrome, low birth weight, premature birth, genetics).

43690084545A4EFA909D43C099B75EC9.description:
List the major milestones of each trimester of fetal development utilizing
medically accurate information.

2EC477B61E2D44B68F13ACB216C9933E.description:
Identify trusted adults, including family members, caregivers, school staff, and
health care professionals to ask questions and discuss pregnancy and other health topics.

5BCE8C09C2C54EDAAD22B386F6DBD34A.description:
Develop a plan to eliminate or reduce risk for unintended pregnancy and/or
STIs (including HIV) and identify ways to overcome potential barriers to prevention.

045D029134A14CC8BDC624A1CBA7DAFE.description:
Compare and contrast the advantages and disadvantages of contraceptive and
disease prevention methods (e.g., abstinence, condoms, emergency contraception, dental
dams).

5E446E828FF34C5496E4C6BE5B82708F.description:
Predict how healthy and unhealthy behaviors can affect brain development
and impact physical, social and emotional stages of early adulthood.

4591EDDBC8834C5AB109A0402AC35A55.description:
Develop a health care plan that includes practices and strategies designed to
support an active lifestyle, attend to mental health, and foster a healthy, social and
emotional life.
